function [CPI] = cpd2cpi(CPD,size,distance)% function [CPI] = cpd2cpi(CPD,size,distance)%% Converts cycles per degree of visual angle [CPD] into cycles per% image [CPI], using [CPD], the [size] of the display, and the% viewing [distance].%% Assumes [size] and [distance] are in the same units.%% March 23, 1997.  JMG  PJB  ABS   U of Toronto Vision LabCPI = rad2deg(atan(size/distance)).*CPD;return